{meta: title Fallen Leaves}
{meta: artist Porter Wagoner}
{meta: composer Louis M. Jones}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Fallen leaves that lie scattered on the [F]ground
[G7]The birds and flowers that were here now can't be [C]found
[F]All the friends that he once knew are not around
[G7]They are scattered like the leaves upon the [C]ground
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[F]Some folks drift along through life and never thrill
[G7]To the feeling that a good deed brings [C]until
[F]It's too late and they are ready to lie down
[G7]There beneath the leaves that scattered on the [C]ground
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]Lord let my eyes see every need of every man
[G7]Make me stop and always lend a helping [C]hand
[F]Then when I'm laid beneath that little grassy mound
[G7]There'll be more friends around than leaves upon the [C]ground
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[F]To your grave there's no use taking any gold
[G7]You cannot use it when it's time for hands to [C]fold
[F]When you leave this earth for a better home someday
[G7]The only thing you'll take is what you gave [C]away
{end_of_verse}
